Residents: Lou-Mari, Sai, Misaki, Daisuke, Erina
Monokuma | Kev 2021-11-23 22:06:26Z
The house of war. Fire, power, and danger emanates from this place. Unlike the other houses, the patch of land around this building has been completely scorched and rendered useless to nature. Wooden barriers with spikes surround the building, as if this place was in the middle of a war. Smoke billows out of the top, and a ladder is the only way up to the front entrance of this thing. The majority of this building seems to have been built out of wood with steel supports. After opening the door, the interior seems to have been inspired by a Viking style of architecture. A large, cozy fireplace is the centerpiece of the house. Items such as wooden shields and bear furs are here. While multitudes of weapons are in here (all of which are dull, might I add), there are also other components of Viking culture. A knitting set is on a table in the corner along with some fishing nets. Horns and torches adorn the walls, and you can see some dried blood splatters scattered around. Interestingly, an altar to an unknown god is also in this house. A single silver crown sits on it, along with two half melted candles. An inscription on the crown reads: "Anyone can hold the helm when the sea is calm, but one becomes a hero only when the storm has arrived." A long, worn, brown cape is hung on the wall. It's made out of a lion's pelt. Subsections in this house also exist, all with wooden ladders that are only partially safe leading up to what appears to be watchtowers. Tall structures with slits in them in order to see the outside are here, watching for a danger that might never come. Up here, you can see all the other houses, but nothing inside the jungle. The thick forestry still covers the interior. (edited)
Six desks and six beds are also in this house. For the house of war, the bedframes and desks are made of wood. The desks contain pencils and sheets of paper. There's a small trash can as well. The four beds are evenly spaced throughout the dorm, each bed with its own desk and lamp, as well as wardrobe that holds clothes. Each desk and wardrobe is locked, and must be unlocked with a Monopad. These locks and the locks on the front door are the only semblance of technology in this place. A bathroom is also linked to here, containing a rustic toilet along with a somewhat working shower. The door does lock, and it's supposed to accommodate for all members of this house. Basic amenities are provided for everyone, despite the house being not so modern. For example, a 21st century sink, bath/shower, and toilet are provided with items like soap and toothbrushes. However, items like a hose from the 19th century that they used to wash out bathrooms are here. A razor from the 17th century seems dull and unsafe to use. Overall, you should be able to use the area. (edited)

Lou-Mari Asencio BOT 2021-12-04 20:21:02Z
Lou-Mari's first destination is this house. Out of the four she saw, this one stuck out to her the most. It feels like something is drawing her to this place, but she can't really explain it. It must be something of the occult right? This seems to be something that would be right up their alley. Having different things that seem basic have differing and broad meanings. This house, the house of war, seems to be the one she wants to explore the most. "Fuck it, no one else is here anyways..." Upon entering the house, Lou-Mari takes everything in. From the watchtowers outside, the inner layout, the various rooms within, it all checks out to her. There's also a sense of unwillingness to go to any of the other houses where she may have to subject herself to the absolute shit that other people may be putting forward. She'll get what she wants from them eventually, but right now it's much too early to even think of her...job... Tossing herself onto one of the beds at random, Lou-Mari stares up at the sealing. Today has been much more eventful than she could've imagined. Thinking of her home now, two names come to mind, but she's not going to mention them out of pain. Pain that this situation she's been subjected to may spell out her end in front of those that she may or may not dislike the most out of humanity. It's case by case... "Yeah, I'll just stick to this place for now I suppose. I'll deal with people when they come. They have something I want, but I can't take it from them yet..." Lou-Mari is actively choosing to stay here. Whoever else may be unfortunate to choose this house will have to deal with her, and she'll have to deal with them. Though that could be a blessing, as Lou-Mari could be someone useful to the right person.
After all, she's The Mediator.
